The assurance has come amid fears that have engulfed Tanzanians living at the border as the neighbouring East African country is electing its leaders today.Speaking separately by Daily News online, Arusha and Kilimanjaro Police Regional Commanders, Charles Mkumbo and Hamis Issah respectively, said security forces were alert to ensure peace and order remain intact.They said all is well and wananchi are going on with their daily business activities as normal.Areas that are experiencing tight security, according to the police are, Longido, Same, Mwanga, Rombo and Siha, districts.On Sunday, the Kilimanjaro RPC told Daily News that Police and local leaders met earlier purposely for sharing intelligence information and strengthening security at borders.